title: Kenya: Muthingi- Ini PB
excerpt:
Filter Roast

With an aroma of chocolate and cherry fragrance. Tasting notes of lemon, raspberry and with a winey finish. It is a little sharp but is sure to impress. 

Varieta: Ruiru 11, SL 28, SL 34, Batman

Process: Wet Processing 

Our recommended filter receipe for this is 15g coffee to 250g of water. Bloom with 60g. After 30 seconds, pour to 120g. Wait another 15 seconds an pour till 180g and then after 10-15s pour consistently until 250g. For bigger brews simply adjust the ratio!

A bit about this coffee,

We sourced this coffee from John Burton LTD.

Muthigi-ini factory was established in 1968 and rests on a 7 acres piece of land serving Cieni, Gaciongo, Kiaragana and Kariko Villages. Currently it is affiliated to Rama Farmers' Cooperative Society Ltd. Its membership currently stands at 2,000. is selectively handpicked and delivered to the wet mill the same day. Red, ripe cherries are separated from under-ripes, over-ripes and foreign matter and the wet mill processing utilizes clean river water that's later re-circulated before it is disposed of in seepage pits. Before the coffee is delivered to the dry mill for secondary processing, it's dried in the sun on traditional raised beds.

title: Brazil - Conquista
excerpt:
Espresso Roast 

With a fragrance of chocolate and marshmallow, notes of buttery biscuit and a clean dark chocolate finish this is one we love with milk based coffee’s!

VARIETAL: Acaia, Yellow Catuai, Yellow Topazio, Red Rubi and Mundo Novo

PROCESS: Natural

A bit about the coffee,

We sourced this green from John Burton Ltd. The coffee is located on a flat topography and features one of the world’s most modern processing infrastructures, including warehouses and a complete container loading structure. It’s high productivity is achieved by applying a mechanical system and using 1500 of its 2000 hectares to produce coffee adopting a highly efficient and a sustainable drop irrigation system.

Surround by the Furnas Lake, the farm is a place of exuberant flora and fauna, set around our Guest house, the Head office and the milling facilities

title: Honduras - Cosagual
excerpt:
Notes of Dark chocolate, butter and hazelnut
Variety: Colombia and Typica
Process: Washed and Sun Dried
We have roasted this coffee to suit all brew methods

For V60 we recommend using 15g ground coffee to 250g water

Bloom to 60g @ 30secs pour 120g

@ 1min pour continuously to 250g

For Espresso use 18g coffee to a 36g extraction in 25-30secs

title: Seasonal Espresso Subscription (6 Monthly Deliveries)
excerpt:
Don’t ever run out of slow coffee at home again. Simply select the options that suit you and we will take care of the rest.

As a subscriber, you are saving 10% on the price of a normal bag of coffee and you will also receive 10% off any other orders you place during the period.

Simply select how much coffee you want per month (250g, 500g, 1kg, or 2kg) we will take care of the rest.

We ship subscription orders the first Tuesday after your order and monthly from there. Your card will be charged monthly after you finish your purchase. You are able to pause or cancel your subscription at any point.

Seasonal espresso subscription is currently only available as whole bean

seoData: {'seoTitle': "Slow Coffee Roaster's Pick Subscription", 'seoDescription': "At Slow Coffee we want our customers to be able to explore coffee's from all around the world. Our roasters pick subscription offers exactly that. Receive a different type of coffee every month from our current offering. Sometimes coffee that aren't currently on offer either.", 'seoHidden': False}

title: Seasonal Espresso Subscription (3 Monthly Deliveries)
excerpt:
Don’t ever run out of slow coffee at home again. Simply select the options that suit you and we will take care of the rest.

As a subscriber, you are saving 10% on the price of a normal bag of coffee and you will also receive 5% off any other orders you place during the period.

Simply select how much coffee you want per month (250g, 500g, 1kg, or 2kg) we will take care of the rest.

We ship subscription orders the first Tuesday after your order and monthly from there. Your card will be charged monthly after you finish your purchase. You are able to pause or cancel your subscription at any point.

Seasonal espresso subscription is currently only available as whole bean

title: Roaster's Pick Subscription (3 Monthly Deliveries)
excerpt:
This is for the home coffee drinker who likes to continually try different coffees.

As a subscriber, you are saving 10% on the price of a normal bag of coffee and you will also receive a code for 10% off your next order

Simply select how much coffee you want (1 or 2 bags per month) we will take care of the rest.

We ship subscription orders the first Tuesday after your order and monthly from there. Your card will be charged monthly after you finish your purchase. You are able to pause or cancel your subscription at any point.
